heaviest_rainfall.status: The heaviest total rainfall occurred on 04 January 2025, dropping 36.8mm of rain over the 37.2 hour storm duration with a maximum rate of 4.6mm per hour.

heaviest_rainrate.status: Today, the rain fell at an intense rate peaking at 16.2mm per hour, one of the heaviest downpours recorded and ranked 4th from our records.  The precipitation lasted 3.9 hours and dumped 8.88mm in total.  The heaviest rain was recorded on 02 September 2025 with a peak rate of 27.0mm per hour.  The storm lasted 15.0 hours and had a total rainfall of 21.19mm.

summary.description:

The past week and month had observable variation in cloud levels (up 1233 m), light levels (up 6623 lux), and rainfall (down 0.6 mm) when compared to today.
